   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Special COVID-19 Relief</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">During the global pandemic, most countries in Southern Africa went into a hard lock down in March 2020. This left many people loosing employment and facing the threat of food insecurity. Loss of income also meant the inability to have hand sanitisers and face masks. HOPE Africa has been working in partnership with communities to raise funds for food distribution, food vouchers, clothing distribution and the distribution of santisers and masks.</narrative>
